sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant HC as HistoricoController
    participant HS as HistoricoService
    participant TR as TurnoRepository
    participant BD as Banco de Dados

    Note over C,BD: 1 · Listagem de eventos (RF014 · RN13)

    C->>+HC: 1. GET /historico?team_id&treadmill_id&athlete_id
    HC->>+HS: 2. listarEventos(filtros)
    HS->>+TR: 3. buscarShifts(filtros)
    TR->>+BD: 4. SELECT Shift + Athlete + Treadmill + Team
    BD-->>-TR: 5. [ { shift, athlete, treadmill, team } ]
    TR-->>-HS: 6. [ { shift, athlete, treadmill, team } ]
    HS->>+TR: 7. buscarCheckpoints(shift_ids[])
    TR->>+BD: 8. SELECT Checkpoints por Shift ORDER DESC
    BD-->>-TR: 9. [ { checkpoint, type, timestamp } ]
    TR-->>-HS: 10. [ { checkpoint, type, timestamp } ]
    HS-->>HS: 11. ordenar — encerramento > checkpoint > início
    HC-->>-C: 12. 200 { eventos[] }
    deactivate HS

    Note over C,BD: 2 · Troca de corredor no histórico (RF020 · RN08)

    C->>+HC: 13. GET /historico?treadmill_id=1
    HC->>+HS: 14. listarEventos({ treadmill_id })
    HS->>+TR: 15. buscarTrocasDeAthlete(treadmill_id)
    TR->>+BD: 16. SELECT Shifts consecutivos por Treadmill
    BD-->>-TR: 17. [ { shift_anterior, shift_novo, timestamp, tipo: "hot_swap" } ]
    TR-->>-HS: 18. [ { shift_anterior, shift_novo, timestamp, tipo: "hot_swap" } ]
    HC-->>-C: 19. 200 { eventos[] tipo "troca_athlete" }
    deactivate HS

    Note over C,BD: 3 · Edição retroativa de checkpoint (RF015 · RN23 · RN24)

    C->>+HC: 20. PATCH /historico/checkpoints/{id} { distance_novo }
    HC->>+HS: 21. editarCheckpoint(checkpoint_id, distance_novo, auditor_id)
    HS->>+TR: 22. buscarCheckpoint(checkpoint_id)
    TR->>+BD: 23. SELECT Checkpoint por id
    BD-->>-TR: 24. { distance_atual, shift_id }
    TR-->>-HS: 25. { distance_atual, shift_id }
    HS->>+TR: 26. buscarAdjacentesShift(shift_id, checkpoint_id)
    TR->>+BD: 27. SELECT Checkpoints anterior e próximo
    BD-->>-TR: 28. { distance_anterior, distance_proximo }
    TR-->>-HS: 29. { distance_anterior, distance_proximo }
    Note right of HS: valida dist_ant <= distance_novo <= dist_prox (RN24)
    HS->>+TR: 30. atualizarCheckpoint(checkpoint_id, distance_novo)
    TR->>+BD: 31. UPDATE Checkpoint SET distance
    BD-->>-TR: 32. ok
    TR-->>-HS: 33. ok
    HS->>+TR: 34. registrarLog(checkpoint_id, anterior, novo, auditor_id)
    TR->>+BD: 35. INSERT Log — imutável (RN23)
    BD-->>-TR: 36. { log_id }
    TR-->>-HS: 37. { log_id }
    HC-->>-C: 38. 200 { checkpoint_id, distance_novo, log_id }
    deactivate HS
